    • executeGet

      public GuiUpdatedValue executeGet(Object target) throws Exception
      execute the property method or obtain the value of the property field
      Parameters:
      target - the property holder, nullable.
      Returns:
      the property value or GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE if the target is null or the property is static
      Throws:
      Exception - it might be caused exception during the execution

    • executeGet

      public GuiUpdatedValue executeGet(Object target, Object prevValue) throws Exception
      execute the property method or obtain the value of the property field if target is null then nothing will happen and always return GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE.
      Parameters:
      target - the property holder
      prevValue - a previous value of the property, which can be compared to the new value and if it equals, the returned value will be GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE.
      Returns:
      the current property value or GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE if no difference from the prevValue
      Throws:
      Exception - it might be caused exception during the method invocation

    • compareGet

      public GuiUpdatedValue compareGet(Object prevValue, Object newValue)
      use Objects.equals(Object, Object) or if GuiTypeValue, use GuiTypeValue.equals(Object, Object).
      Parameters:
      prevValue - the compared value 1
      newValue - the compared value 2
      Returns:
      newValue if equivalent, or GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE.

    • executeSet

      public Object executeSet(Object target, Object value) throws Exception
      execute the setter method or set the value of the property field if the target is null, nothing will happen.
      Parameters:
      target - the field or setter target
      value - the value to be set
      Returns:
      value, or null if error
      Throws:
